Package org.ndnx.ndn.impl.encoding

Interface Summary
XMLCodec Marker interface for XML codecs.
XMLDecoder Each XMLCodec consists effectively of an encoder/decoder pair.
XMLDictionary Defines the API of an XML dictionary.
XMLEncodable Top-level interface implemented by objects that want to make use of our stream encoding and decoding infrastructure.
XMLEncoder  
 

Class Summary
BinaryXMLCodec The ndnb compressed binary XML codec.
BinaryXMLCodec.TypeAndVal Class for managing the paired type/value representation used to encode tags and content lengths.
BinaryXMLDecoder A highly optimized decoder for wire packets.
BinaryXMLEncoder An implementation of XMLEncoder for the Binary (ndnb) codec.
FileBinaryXMLDictionary Encapsulates the mapping from textual XML element and attribute names to the ndnb binary encoding of those elements and attributes.
GenericXMLDecoder This class contains methods for content encoding/decoding common to all or many codecs.
GenericXMLEncodable Implementation of generic XML encode/decode functionality for objects.
GenericXMLEncoder This class contains methods for content encoding/decoding common to all or many codecs.
GenericXMLHandler  
NDNProtocolDictionary Uses the NDNProtocolDTags enum type to implement a dictionary.
NDNProtocolDTags In Java, you can't control the value an enum is assigned to, so we map it into an interior value.
TextXMLCodec A text-based XML codec.
TextXMLDecoder An implementation of XMLDecoder for the Text codec.
TextXMLEncoder An implementation of XMLEncoder for the Text codec.
XMLCodecFactory Factory class that given a string codec name, returns the XMLEncoder and XMLDecoder that handle that codec.
XMLDictionaryStack This class is now only used for the _globalDictionaries static member and the UnknownTag methods.
